cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on task scheduling in a cluster-computing environment. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses load balancing among nodes in a cluster. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a dynamic algorithm for load balancing, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses the divide and conquer principle in its algorithm. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper aims to increase the efficiency of the system.
